      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 249: `onWidthChanged` always treats width changes as authoritative, including programmatic changes caused by `_applyVideoAspectFromHeight()`. This can turn a height-edge resize into two competing adjustments and may save an intermediate geometry depending on signal ordering. Add an explicit adjustment guard so programmatic width/height updates do not re-enter the opposite resize path. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n    property bool _adjustingAspect: false\n\n    function _setAspectGeometry(newWidth, newHeight) {\n        _adjustingAspect \u003d true;\n        if (newWidth !\u003d\u003d width)\n            width \u003d newWidth;\n        if (newHeight !\u003d\u003d height)\n            height \u003d newHeight;\n        _adjustingAspect \u003d false;\n    }\n\n    onWidthChanged: {\n        if (!_adjustingAspect)\n            _applyVideoAspect();\n        saveGeometry();\n    }\n    onHeightChanged: {\n        if (!_adjustingAspect)\n            _applyVideoAspectFromHeight();\n        saveGeometry();\n    }\n```",
      "revId": "a712d52c65837342cd18a8242d46b619ba8affeb",
